#Notes: Can be read by Excel as CSV (Comma Separated Value) or text editor.
#Lines beginning with $ are colors: $Number, RED, GREEN, BLUE, Description, Catalog number
#Lines beginning with * are stitchlist entries: *STITCH, x, y, rel x, rel y, l, a, da
#  *STITCH means needle goes in, *JUMP means needle move only, *COLOR means stop for color change
#  x and y are absolute locations in mm; rel x, rel y are relative locations;
#  If absolute values are blank, relative values are used, otherwise relatives are ignored on read.
#  (This is useful if editing by hand, move a piece of pattern by move first stitch and delete absolute values for the rest.)
#  l is stitch length, a is angle into node, da is angle out - angle in;
#  -999 means not-applicable.  These three parameters are ignored during read.
